<div class="label-content">
  <p>Briar Patch Records is an independent record label founded by Jay Trainer in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. It exists for one reason: to release music that matters — songs built on storytelling, instinct, and the long tradition of artists who choose craft over convenience.</p>

  <p>The name comes from the thickets that grow wild across western Pennsylvania — tangled, resilient, rooted deep in difficult soil. That's the kind of music Briar Patch puts out. Not polished for algorithms. Not shaped by trends. Grown slowly, with intention, and released when it's ready.</p>

  <div class="about-quote">
    "Some music is made to be consumed. This music is made to be lived with."
  </div>

  <p>Every release on the label — from the raw, unpolished live recordings of <em>The Waking Hours</em> to the expanded, firelight-recorded <em>A Whisper of Ruin — Deluxe Edition</em> — reflects a philosophy of patience and authenticity. No rushing a record to meet a deadline. No cutting corners on the sound.</p>

  <p>Briar Patch Records is currently home to Jay Trainer's complete catalogue: eight releases spanning nearly two decades of folk, acoustic rock, and Americana. The label is always looking forward — new recordings, new collaborations, new chapters in the story.</p>

  <h3 class="label-heading">Explore the Catalogue</h3>
  <p>Every album, single, and live recording released through Briar Patch Records is available to stream and download.</p>
